<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861230-0093 </DOCNO><HL> Erb Chairman CompletesPurchase of Firm's Shares</HL><DD> 12/30/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> BIRMINGHAM, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Fred A. Erb, chairman, chiefexecutive officer and president of Erb Lumber Co. completedthe previously announced purchase of all the company's sharesoutstanding for $17 a share, or $21 million, the companysaid.   Erb Lumber said stockholders approved the plan at a special meeting yesterday. Prior to the acquisition, Mr. Erb's family held about 62.4%, or about 2.2 million, of the 3.25 million shares outstanding, a company spokesman said.    Mr. Erb founded Fredco Inc. to acquire the entire equity interest of Erb Lumber. Under the transaction, Erb Lumber will retain its name and continue to do business as a closely held company. Erb Lumber, which sells lumber and building materials, had third-quarter net income of $2.9 million, or 90 cents a share, on sales of $83 million. </TEXT></DOC>